    "summary": "Hello! I'm a computer scientist fascinated by how technology can offer new affordances and create opportunities for adaptive and innovative pedagogies. I like to design and develop technologies that could add value for the learner and the teacher. In my academic journey so far I have been fortunate to work with highly multidisciplinary and multicultural teams in Greece, Qatar, Macau SAR China, Denmark, and the Netherlands. I'm also honoured to serve as a committee member (2022-2026) in the CSCL community of the International Society of the Learning Sciences.\n\nMy current projects involve, among others, the development of AI pedagogical agents for collaborative learning (started years ago with MentorChat and colMOOC and continuing with Clair), learning analytics and automated feedback for professional learning communities, tangible interfaces for programming and collaboration, and audience response systems for classroom engagement and self-awareness.\n\nInnovation and creativity around educational technology is my main drive and I'm constantly looking for new ideas, projects, and opportunities to collaborate.",
